### Bank Account Management System Demo
### If you use VS Code, install the "REST Client" extension. 
### You will see a small "Send Request" button above each command below. 
### Simply click it to run the demo live in your video!

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@accountId = demo-acc-777
@timestamp = {{$datetime iso8601}}

### 1. Create a New Bank Account
# Expected: 202 Accepted
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountId": "{{accountId}}",
  "ownerName": "Alice Smith",
  "initialBalance": 0,
  "currency": "USD"
}

###

### 2. Deposit Money (First Transaction)
# Expected: 202 Accepted
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/deposit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 500.00,
  "description": "Salary Deposit",
  "transactionId": "txn-deposit-1"
}

###

### 3. Withdraw Money (Second Transaction)
# Expected: 202 Accepted
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/withdraw
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 100.00,
  "description": "ATM Withdrawal",
  "transactionId": "txn-withdraw-1"
}

###

### 4. Overdraft Prevention (Domain Logic validation)
# Expected: 409 Conflict (amount exceeds balance)
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/withdraw
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 1000.00,
  "description": "Buying a TV",
  "transactionId": "txn-withdraw-2"
}

###

### 5. Check Current Account State (CQRS Read side)
# Expected: 200 OK (Balance should be 400.00)
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}

###

### 6. View Transaction History (Projection)
# Expected: 200 OK (Paginated list showing the 500 deposit and 100 withdrawal)
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/transactions?page=1&pageSize=10

###

### 7. View Raw Event Stream (Audit Log)
# Expected: 200 OK (Shows AccountCreated, MoneyDeposited, MoneyWithdrawn events)
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/events

###

### 8. Idempotency Test (Duplicate Transaction ID)
# Expected: 202 Accepted (but balance won't change because the ID is tracked!)
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/deposit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 500.00,
  "description": "Salary Deposit",
  "transactionId": "txn-deposit-1"
}

###

### 9. Check Projection Engine Status
# Expected: 200 OK (Shows lag: 0)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projections/status

###

### 10. Close Account (Fails because balance is not 0)
# Expected: 409 Conflict
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}/close
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Moving countries"
}
